        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 2:22PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles north of Chinook, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Blaine County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
